<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef9d08a8-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s300302"><num value="300302">§ 300302.</num><heading> Certified local government</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this division, the term “certified local government” means a local government whose local historic preservation program is certified pursuant to chapter 3025 of this title.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idef9d08a9-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">(<ref href="/us/pl/113/287/s3">Pub. L. 113–287, § 3</ref>, <date date="2014-12-19">Dec. 19, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/3188">128 Stat. 3188</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
